plant and fruits of 
<taxonomicName id="631255FF3CD3738B8DD7F0C109EC0509" genus="B." lsidName="B. acetosella" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="acetosella">
<emphasis id="4B8D9E0BE2DAC18C21C63E13C5CDA0BA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. acetosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="5D71C0FE0EB83C21B3A430263AD9D750" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">E, F</emphasis>
male and female flowering plants of 
<taxonomicName id="21099909FEA5A59A102FA57B6051E958" genus="B." lsidName="B. handelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="handelii">
<emphasis id="32AD0E4007CA31AEAA6F21C0EBBEA753" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. handelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3FB424D88AD59BF0F0C458A170BF3950" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="21711BCD8A6A4BF4632151655B187BAC" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Distribution and phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1EE27EE3243AEF8F6D6B32C36DF24B13" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="4F2AA3118C870F89AC6E107BBDBEB4A8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">China</emphasis>
: Yunnan, Lancang, only seen in type locality, alt. 1600 m; 
<emphasis id="7206FD642CC83FB60DAA79C890C75DF3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Laos</emphasis>
: Luang Namtha Province, Nam Ha National Biodiversity Conservation Area, Near Na Lun Village, alt. 687 m (
<bibRefCitation id="0E5AB597096F9FE0F0F2A0E672C7EEBD" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.138.46718" author="Ding, HB" journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="187 - 301" refId="B11" refString="Ding, HB, Maw, MB, Yang, B, Bouamanivong, S, Tan, YH, 2020. An updated checklist of Begonia (Begoniaceae) in Laos, with two new species and five new records. PhytoKeys 137: 187 - 301, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.138.46718" title="An updated checklist of Begonia (Begoniaceae) in Laos, with two new species and five new records." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.138.46718" volume="137" year="2020">Ding et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Flowering March to May, fruiting April to July.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3F83953245786FBB5C2021E99FD0EFD5" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="34A60240ADD28B6EF63EAFCCFFAD6506" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CB85BDFFA6F3F1B509D54B891F3027CD" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
Regionally Extinct (RE). The living plants of 
<taxonomicName id="9E9411220F33E7BE60306E9A11236F90" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Begonia" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Begonia</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="F737FA54C52DEFDA5529259DE8FE90C8" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="FC4E263865C85DBE8A0F7A3B6C2F48E6" authorityName="S. H. Huang" authorityYear="1999" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="lancangensis" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lancangensis">lancangensis</taxonomicName>
have not been found in the type locality during field surveys after its first description. Recently, however, other researchers found wild plants in Laos (
<bibRefCitation id="9C0F7AF0B6961AF81385325B8FBE93D1" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.138.46718" author="Ding, HB" journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="187 - 301" refId="B11" refString="Ding, HB, Maw, MB, Yang, B, Bouamanivong, S, Tan, YH, 2020. An updated checklist of Begonia (Begoniaceae) in Laos, with two new species and five new records. PhytoKeys 137: 187 - 301, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.138.46718" title="An updated checklist of Begonia (Begoniaceae) in Laos, with two new species and five new records." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.138.46718" volume="137" year="2020">Ding et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1F2646B1CA8D70D9C3A9A049A186616D" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="E32F2B8306D8CCC5E27CADC12FC61657" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD3BD2F24E31F5C4DA66481C61524545" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
Like 
<taxonomicName id="4DF9C59C6A9CDBFDB4A217069E3F5753" genus="B." lsidName="B. acetosella" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="acetosella">
<emphasis id="66D9752871A70A719AE2B8BCF2E65ED9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. acetosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="656CCD09343CF27B614D837CEF0B6DE8" genus="B." lsidName="B. handelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="handelii">
<emphasis id="2125406B2A7905E95D9A1F81059893B8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. handelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F3E235D558C02FA9D5800A86DD069F7C" genus="B." lsidName="B. silletensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="silletensis">
<emphasis id="0448D9B334F37E70FD8897185673D440" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. silletensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
C.B.Clarke (
<bibRefCitation id="5EBEED2991A425C5F32E691895AA0D11" author="Clarke, CB" journalOrPublisher=") Flora of British India" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="635 - 636" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/37371521[accessed" refId="B5" refString="Clarke, CB, 1879. Begoniaceae. In: Hooker JD (Ed.) Flora of British India 2: 635 - 636, https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/37371521[accessed" title="Begoniaceae. In: Hooker JD (Ed." url="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/37371521[accessed" volume="2" year="1879">Clarke 1879</bibRefCitation>
), dioecious 
<taxonomicName id="8DD1FE0E9A80A5F43AAC318B50837B3B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Begonia" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Begonia</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="1F1B2B8AFB4E4297A30879F620DFE671" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="E7DE99C22FC01CFA4E69C66F78018190" authorityName="S. H. Huang" authorityYear="1999" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="lancangensis" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lancangensis">lancangensis</taxonomicName>
has berry-like fruits and was previously classified in section 
<taxonomicName id="12FE120C48E97E8BEF3EDF3B3C3DB56D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Sphenanthera">Sphenanthera</taxonomicName>
, but has recently been integrated into section 
<taxonomicName id="C2E47441FA79AB319D5074CAF89139D9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Platycentrum">Platycentrum</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BCC1AA86AD8F9609F6FE4144898EA4C7" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/672.3" author="Moonlight, PW" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="267 - 323" refId="B31" refString="Moonlight, PW, Ardi, WH, Padilla, LA, Chung, KF, Fuller, D, Girmansyah, D, Hollands, R, Jara-Munoz, A, Kiew, R, Leong, WC, Liu, Y, Mahardika, A, Marasinghe, LDK, O'Connor, M, Peng, C-I, Perez, AJ, Phutthai, T, Pullan, M, Rajbhandary, S, Reynel, C, Rubite, RR, Sang, J, Scherberich, D, Shui, YM, Tebbitt, MC, Thomas, DC, Wilson, HP, Zaini, NH, Hughes, M, 2018. Dividing and conquering the fastest-growing genus: Towards a natural sectional classification of the mega-diverse genus Begonia (Begoniaceae). Taxon 67 (2): 267 - 323, DOI: https://doi.org/10.12705/672.3" title="Dividing and conquering the fastest-growing genus: Towards a natural sectional classification of the mega-diverse genus Begonia (Begoniaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/672.3" volume="67" year="2018">Moonlight et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). In the wild, 
<taxonomicName id="A1AE1BE58883D246804198DDDE74E700" genus="B." lsidName="B. acetosella" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="acetosella">
<emphasis id="AE20003F507FCFC1F28A387BBC699ACC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. acetosella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="315C215EB1605823B3796D847CF84BB5" genus="B." lsidName="B. handelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="handelii">
<emphasis id="17A70AB4758BC8C152B2AB7B3F25392B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. handelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B3A600DFADC644A55EE644CEC8E81B29" genus="B." lsidName="B. silletensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="silletensis">
<emphasis id="BDB805FC4929832E7AAE2B3FB58ADB92" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">B. silletensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
often have overlapping distributions, meaning natural cross fertilisation is possible due to their overlapping flowering periods. The hybrid plants are usually very few and, therefore, rarely observed, due to a low chance of a natural cross. Natural crossings may generate new hybrids in the future.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
